# API Overview

sslm.ols(formula, data)

Runs OLS regression using formula syntax.

Parameters
	â€¢	formula â€” string, e.g., "y ~ x1 + x2"
	â€¢	data â€” pandas DataFrame

Returns
	â€¢	SSLM_Model object

â¸»

model.summary()

Prints APA-style regression output including:
	â€¢	unstandardized coefficients (B)
	â€¢	standard errors
	â€¢	standardized beta (Î²)
	â€¢	t-values & p-values
	â€¢	semi-partial RÂ² (srÂ²)
	â€¢	model-level fit stats (RÂ², Adj. RÂ², F, etc.)

â¸»

model.as_dataframe()

Returns the full coefficient table as a pandas DataFrame
(ideal for exporting to Excel, LaTeX, or APA tables).

